.TH WORKCELL 1 "2026-03-22" "Workcell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
workcell \- bounded runtime launcher for coding agents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B workcell
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fB--\fR \fIprovider-args\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B workcell
starts the selected coding agent inside a bounded local runtime with explicit
isolation and policy controls.
The Tier 1 path is a dedicated Colima virtual machine profile on macOS plus a
hardened container inside that VM.
The managed runtime mounts
.I /tmp
as
.B noexec
and uses
.I /state/tmp
as the exec-capable temporary directory via
.BR TMPDIR .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --agent codex|claude|gemini
Select the provider to run. The default is
.BR codex .
.TP
.B --ui cli|gui
Select the surface to launch. Only
.BR cli
is currently implemented as a preserved-boundary path.
.TP
.B --mode strict|build|breakglass
Select the runtime profile. The default is
.BR strict .
.TP
.B --ack-breakglass
Required with
.B --mode breakglass
to make the higher-trust path explicit.
.TP
.B --ack-arbitrary-command
Required with
.B --allow-arbitrary-command
to make lower-assurance boundary-debugging command passthrough explicit.
.TP
.B --workspace PATH
Select the workspace to mount inside the runtime. The default is the current
directory.
.TP
.B --allow-nongit-workspace
Allow a non-git workspace that contains an explicit agent marker file.
.TP
.B --allow-arbitrary-command
Launch the runtime image with a direct container entrypoint after
.BR -- .
This is intended only for lower-assurance boundary debugging and is recorded in
the host audit log as a downgraded path.
.TP
.B --colima-profile NAME
Override the derived Colima profile name.
.TP
.B --rebuild
Rebuild the runtime image before launch.
This is rejected on
.BR strict ;
seed or refresh the reviewed image through
.BR build
first.
.TP
.B --dry-run
Print the selected runtime command and exit.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show usage information.
.SH PROFILES
.TP
.B strict
Allowlisted network access only, no host credential or control socket
passthrough, and provider-native bounded or constrained mode only where the
selected provider actually offers one. On this profile, direct native ELF
execution from mutable
.I /workspace
and
.I /state
paths is blocked, and mutable shebang scripts cannot target protected real
runtimes directly.
This profile requires a prebuilt reviewed runtime image and does not perform
cold builds or rebuilds.
.TP
.B build
The same mount and secret restrictions as
.BR strict ,
with broader network access for dependency and build traffic.
Reviewed runtime-image creation and rebuilds happen here.
.TP
.B breakglass
Still inside the Workcell VM plus container boundary, but with unrestricted
network access. The managed entrypoint does not auto-inject unsafe provider
flags; any adapter-specific high-trust launch is a lower-assurance direct
provider path. This profile requires
.BR --ack-breakglass .
.SH NODE SURFACE
The public
.B node
surface exposed by the managed runtime is intended for workspace JavaScript, not
for launching provider entrypoints, repackaged workspace copies of the shipped
provider package trees, or loading native addons. Workcell blocks those paths
on the safe profiles so public
.B node
execution cannot retake unmediated native code execution.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/workcell
Installed launcher path used by
.BR scripts/install.sh .
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/man/man1/workcell.1
Installed man page path used by
.BR scripts/install.sh .
.TP
.I ~/.colima/PROFILE/workcell.audit.log
Durable host-side audit log written by the managed launcher for real runs.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The command exits non-zero on validation failures, unsupported modes, missing
dependencies, or runtime launch errors.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR colima (1),
.BR docker (1)
